üîπ BASIC LEVEL MCQs (10)
1. PCI DSS is primarily designed to protect:
A. Healthcare data
B. Payment cardholder data
C. Financial audit logs
D. Intellectual property

2. PCI DSS applies to organizations that:
A. Store employee data
B. Process, store, or transmit card data
C. Use ISO standards
D. Conduct audits

3. PCI DSS was developed by:
A. ISO
B. PCI Security Standards Council
C. NIST
D. CIS

4. The main goal of PCI DSS is to:
A. Improve network speed
B. Reduce payment card fraud
C. Replace ISO 27001
D. Improve coding practices

5. Which of the following is PCI DSS data?
A. PAN (Primary Account Number)
B. Employee ID
C. System hostname
D. Source code

6. PCI DSS compliance is:
A. Voluntary
B. Mandatory for card handlers
C. Optional guideline
D. Only for banks

7. CIS Critical Security Controls are best described as:
A. Legal regulations
B. Prioritized security best practices
C. Audit penalties
D. Incident reports

8. CIS Controls are designed to:
A. Replace ISO and NIST
B. Reduce cyber risks effectively
C. Improve financial reporting
D. Conduct audits

9. CIS Benchmarks mainly provide:
A. Legal compliance
B. Secure configuration guidelines
C. Penetration testing scripts
D. Malware signatures

10. CIS Controls are MOST useful for:
A. Hackers
B. Organizations of all sizes
C. Law enforcement
D. End users only

üî∏ INTERMEDIATE LEVEL MCQs (10)
11. PCI DSS history started due to:
A. Healthcare breaches
B. Increasing credit card fraud
C. Cloud adoption
D. GDPR enforcement

12. PCI DSS Level classification is based on:
A. Organization size
B. Number of transactions processed annually
C. Number of audits
D. Network size

13. Which PCI level applies to merchants processing over 6 million transactions?
A. Level 4
B. Level 3
C. Level 2
D. Level 1

14. PCI DSS Level 1 merchants require:
A. Self-assessment only
B. External audit by QSA
C. No assessment
D. Internal review only

15. PCI DSS requires organizations to:
A. Eliminate all risks
B. Protect cardholder data environment (CDE)
C. Replace IT controls
D. Avoid audits

16. CIS Controls follow which core principle?
A. Compliance first
B. Risk-based prioritization
C. Financial auditing
D. Legal enforcement

17. CIS Controls v8 are grouped into:
A. 5 domains
B. 10 domains
C. 18 controls
D. 25 controls

18. CIS Compliance means:
A. Following all laws
B. Implementing CIS Controls and Benchmarks
C. Getting ISO certification
D. Passing audits

19. CIS Benchmarks help auditors by:
A. Providing evidence templates
B. Defining secure baseline configurations
C. Replacing audits
D. Eliminating vulnerabilities

20. PCI DSS focuses MOST on which security objective?
A. Availability
B. Confidentiality of card data
C. Performance
D. Scalability

üî¥ ADVANCED LEVEL MCQs (10)
21. PCI DSS scope reduction can be achieved by:
A. Increasing documentation
B. Network segmentation
C. Ignoring controls
D. Avoiding audits

22. PCI DSS is different from ISO 27001 because PCI DSS is:
A. Risk-based
B. Industry-specific and mandatory
C. Management-driven
D. Voluntary

23. A major challenge in PCI DSS compliance is:
A. Tool availability
B. Identifying complete cardholder data flow
C. Staff training
D. Reporting format

24. CIS Controls are considered implementation-focused because they:
A. Are laws
B. Provide actionable steps
C. Replace governance
D. Eliminate risk

25. CIS Benchmarks are MOST useful during which audit activity?
A. Risk identification
B. Configuration review
C. Financial audit
D. Incident response

26. PCI DSS Level 4 merchants usually validate compliance through:
A. External audit
B. Self-Assessment Questionnaire (SAQ)
C. No validation
D. Regulatory approval

27. CIS Controls complement other frameworks like NIST and ISO by:
A. Replacing them
B. Providing technical implementation guidance
C. Acting as law
D. Eliminating audits

28. From CCEE exam view, PCI DSS questions MOSTLY test:
A. Penalty amounts
B. Scope, levels, and core objective
C. Encryption algorithms
D. Coding standards

29. CIS Controls are prioritized based on:
A. Cost
B. Known attack patterns
C. Auditor preference
D. Compliance laws

30. An organization using CIS Benchmarks improves:
A. Network speed
B. System hardening and security posture
C. Incident response time only
D. Compliance penalties

